                <head>No. 8.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Lord <persName type="from">Sackville</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-10-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 30, 1888</date>. (Received October
                        31.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of this day’s date, informing me that the President of the United
                    States has become convinced that it would be incompatible with the best
                    interests and detrimental to the good relations of both Governments that I
                    should any longer hold my present official position in the United States, and
                    transmitting my passports.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sackville.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
